# Steps before starting the project:
1) Download python 3.8 and above >> python -V
2) Download pip >> pip -V
** pip install virtualenv
3) create an environment
** virtualenv testenv "or" python -m venv testenv
4) activate the environment
>> go to the environment file then Scripts the activate
** testenv\Scripts\acticate
5) to deactivate the environment
** deactivate
6) Download django
** pip install django
7) go to the environment file then start the project
** cd testenv
** django-admin startproject testproject
>> you will get testproject file and manage.python
8) go to the project file and runserver
** cd testproject
** python manage.py runserver